        <p:txBody>
          <a:bodyPr wrap="square" lIns="182880" tIns="91440" rIns="182880" bIns="91440" rtlCol="0" anchor="ctr"/>
          <a:lstStyle/>
          <a:p>
            <a:pPr indent="0" marL="0"><a:buNone/></a:pPr>
            <a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1100" b="1" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="EF4444"/></a:solidFill></a:rPr><a:t xml:space="preserve">Q: “How do you know the 90-day window is correct?” </a:t></a:r>
            <a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1100" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="CADCFC"/></a:solidFill></a:rPr><a:t>v1 assumption aligned to PANW’s quarterly comp cycle. Validate against renewal cohorts at 12–18 months. Segment-specific windows are v2.</a:t></a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
      </p:sp>

      <!-- Q2 -->
      <p:sp>
        <p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="20" name="Q2Bg"/><p:cNvSpPr/><p:nvPr/></p:nvSpPr>
        <p:spPr>
          <a:xfrm><a:off x="457200" y="1774440"/><a:ext cx="8229600" cy="548640"/></a:xfrm>
          <a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom>
          <a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="1A2558"/></a:solidFill>
          <a:ln><a:noFill/></a:ln>
        </p:spPr>
        <p:txBody>
          <a:bodyPr wrap="square" lIns="182880" tIns="91440" rIns="182880" bIns="91440" rtlCol="0" anchor="ctr"/>
          <a:lstStyle/>
          <a:p>
            <a:pPr indent="0" marL="0"><a:buNone/></a:pPr>
            <a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1100" b="1" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="EF4444"/></a:solidFill></a:rPr><a:t xml:space="preserve">Q: “What if reps game the metric?” </a:t></a:r>
            <a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1100" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="CADCFC"/></a:solidFill></a:rPr><a:t>90-day smoothing prevents week-of-quarter spikes. Real risk is inverse: pushing unnecessary scans. Flagged as v1 limitation — engagement quality signal is the v2 mitigation.</a:t></a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
      </p:sp>

      <!-- Q3 -->
